HEADWORD: Corbiestep
<hw>Cor"bie*step`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>One of the steps in which a gable wall is often finished in place
of a continuous slope; -- also called
<altname>crowstep</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

